<HEADLINE>
FT  09 MAY 94 / UK Company News: P&amp;P purchase for up to Pounds 6.6m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
P&amp;P, the computer hardware supplier and services company, is buying
Computers for Business (Scotland) for up to Pounds 6.6m.
The company also reported an encouraging start to the present year to
November 30 1994.
Profitable contributions continued to be made by most areas of the business
and earnings were showing significant progress. An initial Pounds 3.74m for
94.3 per cent of CFB will be satisfied by the issue of 4.5m shares, valued
at Pounds 3.11m, Pounds 520,724 in loan notes and Pounds 108,597 cash. P&amp;P
has an option to buy the outstanding shares for an initial Pounds 260,000
cash.
A further Pounds 1m payment is variable depending on net assets at
completion and there is an additional profit-related payment to a maximum of
Pounds 1.6m.
The additional payments will be satisfied by a mixture of shares, loan notes
and cash.
CFB reported 1993 pre-tax profits of Pounds 530,157 (Pounds 606,000) on
turnover of Pounds 15m (Pounds 12.1m).
</TEXT>
