<HEADLINE>
FT  09 MAY 94 / Observer: Novel delights
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A visitor to the smart new Gresham Street headquarters of College Hill
Associates, a London PR firm, was much taken with the fancy wallpaper in one
meeting room, cunningly disguised, trompe l'oeil fashion, as book spines.
The 'shelves' are adorned with classic authors like Ibsen, Dante, Shaw,
Racine and Austin. Austin?
Must be the little-known British linguistic philosopher J L Austin, rather
than the more famous Jane Austen. Adds a touch of class to the place,
doesn't it?
