FT  09 MAY 94 / London may buck job trend
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID GOODHART, Labour Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
London will buck the trend towards replacing full-time jobs with part-time
ones, and its manufacturing companies are set to create more jobs than those
in financial services, says a report published today.
The survey of 1,000 companies by Centec, central London's Training and
Enterprise Council, found twice as many would increase full-time jobs as
would create part-time jobs.
Mrs Gwynneth Flower, Centec chief executive, said: 'This could be one of the
first real indications that full-time employment is coming back, and that
London is leading the way.'
Business services and manufacturing anticipate most growth in full time jobs
over the next three years. However, financial services companies continue to
expect a net reduction in staff.
